<p>I am running in a situation where i have to connect two composite with edge. This edge could be redraw if size of any composite change. I register a paintListener on my base composite to connect the child composite. But every time when paintListener execute it draw a new edge but it does not remove the previous edge. Below is my code.</p>  <p>Please help me to overcome this situation.</p>  <pre><code>addPaintListener(new PaintListener() {     @Override     public void paintControl(PaintEvent pe) {      for (Point[] line : points) {         pe.gc.setLineWidth(2);         pe.gc.drawLine(line[0].x, line[0].y, line[1].x, line[1].y);         int[] xPoints = { line[1].x - 8, line[1].x, line[1].x + 8 };         int[] yPoints = { line[1].y - 8, line[1].y, line[1].y - 8 };         pe.gc.setBackground(getDisplay().getSystemColor(SWT.COLOR_BLACK));         pe.gc.fillPolygon(new int[] { xPoints[0], yPoints[0], xPoints[1], yPoints[1], xPoints[2],             yPoints[2] });     }     pe.gc.dispose();     } }); </code></pre>